  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "The behavior of webpack `require` differs between regular React components and React stateless functional components.\n\nThis will work:\n\n```\nvar Component = React.createClass({\n    render: function() {\n        return (\n      <div>\n        <h1>Component</h1>\n        <img src={require('./test.png')}/>\n      </div>\n        );\n    }\n});\n```\n\nThis will not:\n\n```\nvar StatelessFunctionalComponent = props => (\n  <div>\n    <h1>Stateless Functional Component</h1>\n    <img src={require('./test.png')}/>\n  </div>\n);\n```\n\nSee https://github.com/abloomston/webpack-react-require-problem for a simple project that reproduces this issue.\n\nApologies in advance if I am making an obvious mistake in my configuration.\n",
